   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <p>At least one saved filter exists. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on saving a filter, refer to <xref href="SaveFltr.xml">Saving a Filter</xref>.</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context>You can delete the saved filter. The following procedure describes the steps to delete a filter. The <uicontrol>PROJECTS</uicontrol> list page is used here as an example.</context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Projects</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p>The list of projects you are invited to is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the tool bar, click <image href="../../Icons/Filter-Toolbar.png" placement="inline">
                  <alt>Filter</alt>
               </image> . </p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>FILTERS</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>Select Filter</uicontrol> section, select the appropriate filter. </p>
            <p>Available options are filters defined for the page. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on defining a filter, refer to <xref href="SaveFltr.xml">Saving a Filter</xref>.</ph>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <image href="../../Icons/DelFilter.png" placement="inline">
                  <alt>Delete</alt>
               </image> to delete the selected filter. </p>
            <p>A confirmation message is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
